\newlabel{fig:continuous}{{2}{5}{Continuous feature distributions by income class. \texttt {education\_num}, \texttt {age}, and \texttt {hours\_per\_week} show clear class separation. \texttt {capital\_gain} and \texttt {capital\_loss} are dominated by the zero mass and long right tails, making the Gaussian summary a poor description of their shape}{figure.caption.2}{}}
